With empty glass bottles, cardboard boxes, discarded appliances and pieces of old wooden furniture piled high outside the home, it has not been lived in by its occupants for years. 

But the Bondi hoarders still inhabit the front and back yards of the Boonara Avenue house, guarding their piles of trash as if it is treasure. 

Plastic bags full of rubbish, old paint tins, a rusted wheelbarrow and a suitcase have caused the gates to almost burst at the seams as they hold back the mountains of trash.   

